3. Integrar Alpine.js para interatividade em tempo real
4. Adicionar ordenação por colunas (nome, fscs, validade)

1. Criar migration para tabela 'notifications':
   - id, user_id, credential_id, type (expiring_30/expiring_7/expired), read_at, sent_at, timestamps
2. Criar Command 'CheckExpiringCredentials':
   ```php
   public function handle() {
       $expiring30 = Credential::whereBetween('validity', [now(), now()->addDays(30)])->get();
       $expiring7 = Credential::whereBetween('validity', [now(), now()->addDays(7)])->get();

       foreach ($expiring30 as $cred) {
           Notification::firstOrCreate([
               'credential_id' => $cred->id,
               'type' => 'expiring_30'
           ], ['user_id' => $cred->created_by]);
       }
       // Similar para expiring_7
   }
   ```
3. Agendar comando no Kernel.php:
   ```php
   $schedule->command('credentials:check-expiring')->daily();
   ```
